        },
        {
            "title": "Meta簽署規模達數吉瓦的核電協議 為人工智能數據中心供電",
            "description": "<div class=\"atoms\"><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\"><span class=\"news-dateline\">【彭博】--</span> Meta Platforms Inc.已為其數據中心達成一系列電力協議，這將使其在超大規模雲服務商同行中成為核電的最大買家。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">這些協議最終規模可能合計超過6吉瓦，足以為一座約有500萬戶家庭規模的城市供電。在人工智能主導權爭奪愈發激烈之際，這些交易表明，大型科技公司為鎖定電力供應而展開的競賽仍未放緩。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">Meta周五表示，將從Vistra Corp.三座現有電廠購買電力，並支持若干座小型反應堆，這些反應堆是由Sam Altman投資的Oklo Inc.以及比爾·蓋茲投資的TerraPower LLC計畫在未來十年內建設的。而去年6月，Meta已達成協議，從Constellation Energy Corp.一處核電站獲取電力。</p><div class=\"bg-toast-background -mx-5 -mt-2 mb-3 pb-3 md:-mx-0 lg:mx-auto lg:w-[300px] lg:pb-0\"><div class=\"text-px14 text-gandalf py-1 text-center leading-5\">廣告</div><div class=\"mx-auto text-center min-w-[300px] min-h-[250px]\" id=\"sda-inbody-a29e220d-f42f-3eef-ac73-11cf918a90ba-1-iframe\"><div class=\"bg-dirty-seagull text-px12 text-dolphin mx-auto hidden items-center justify-center only:flex w-[300px] h-[250px]\">廣告</div></div></div><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">周五紐約盤前，Vistra股價上漲10%；Oklo股價上漲約20%。</p><div class=\"recommendation-contents\"><div class=\"bg-marshmallow mb-2 h-[30px] w-[80px] rounded-lg\"></div><div class=\"no-scrollbar -mx-5 mb-5 flex overflow-hidden overflow-x-auto md:-mx-2 lg:mb-3.5\"><div class=\"bg-marshmallow mr-2 ml-5 h-[92px] w-[calc(85%-28px)] flex-shrink-0 rounded-lg md:ml-2 md:w-[calc(85%-16px)] lg:h-[120px] lg:w-[calc(50%-16px)]\"></div><div class=\"bg-marshmallow mx-2 h-[92px] w-[85%] flex-shrink-0 rounded-lg lg:h-[120px] lg:w-[calc(50%-16px)]\"></div></div></div><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">原文標題Meta Signs Multi-Gigawatt Nuclear Deals for AI Data Centers (1)</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">--聯合報導 Naureen S Malik.</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">More stories like this are available on <a class=\"link\" data-ylk=\"slk:bloomberg.com;elm:context_link;itc:0;sec:content-canvas\" href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">bloomberg.com</a></p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">©2026 Bloomberg L.P.</p></div>",
            "link": "https://hk.news.yahoo.com/meta%E7%B0%BD%E7%BD%B2%E8%A6%8F%E6%A8%A1%E9%81%94%E6%95%B8%E5%90%89%E7%93%A6%E7%9A%84%E6%A0%B8%E9%9B%BB%E5%8D%94%E8%AD%B0-%E7%82%BA%E4%BA%BA%E5%B7%A5%E6%99%BA%E8%83%BD%E6%95%B8%E6%93%9A%E4%B8%AD%E5%BF%83%E4%BE%9B%E9%9B%BB-120310658.html",
